@startuml

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #333
  LifeLineBorderColor #1565C0
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  ParticipantBorderColor #1565C0
}

title Route Computation Pipeline - UML Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Browser\n(dash-leaflet)" as Browser
participant "map_callbacks.py" as Callbacks
participant "route_job.py\n<<background thread>>" as Pipeline
participant "namelist_writer.py" as Namelist
participant "env_data_downloader.py" as EnvDL
participant "Copernicus\nMarine API" as Copernicus
participant "visir_api.py\n<<HTTP client>>" as VisirAPI
participant "visir_runner.py\n<<Flask :5050>>" as VisirRunner
participant "MAIN_Campi" as Campi
participant "MAIN_Tracce" as Tracce

== Submit Route Request ==

User -> Browser : Fill route form\n(origin, dest, vessel,\ndeparture, forcing)
Browser -> Callbacks : submit_route_form()
activate Callbacks
Callbacks -> Pipeline : create_job(job_id)\nrun_pipeline(job_id, params)
Callbacks --> Browser : Close modal,\nshow progress panel
deactivate Callbacks

activate Pipeline

== Step 1: params ==

Pipeline -> Namelist : create_namelists(params)
activate Namelist
Namelist --> Pipeline : YAML files created\n(_a_Grafi, _b_Campi, _d_Tracce)
deactivate Namelist

== Step 2: data ==

Pipeline -> EnvDL : download_env_data(start, end, forcing)
activate EnvDL
EnvDL -> Copernicus : copernicusmarine.subset()\n(wave: VHM0, VMDR)\n(current: Current, Currentdir)
Copernicus --> EnvDL : NetCDF files
EnvDL --> Pipeline : env files saved to\n__data/envFields/
deactivate EnvDL

== Step 3: fields ==

Pipeline -> VisirAPI : run_campi("tyrr_fields")
activate VisirAPI
VisirAPI -> VisirRunner : POST /run-campi
activate VisirRunner
VisirRunner -> Campi : Main(jobName="tyrr_fields")
activate Campi
note right of Campi : Reads env NetCDF,\ninterpolates onto\ngraph edges
Campi --> VisirRunner : fields processed
deactivate Campi
VisirRunner --> VisirAPI : 200 OK
deactivate VisirRunner
VisirAPI --> Pipeline : success
deactivate VisirAPI

== Step 4: routes ==

Pipeline -> VisirAPI : run_route("tyrr_route", run_name)
activate VisirAPI
VisirAPI -> VisirRunner : POST /run
activate VisirRunner
VisirRunner -> Tracce : Main(jobName="tyrr_route")
activate Tracce
note right of Tracce : Dijkstra on\nweighted graph.\nProduces 3 routes:\n- shortest distance\n- fastest time\n- lowest CO₂
Tracce --> VisirRunner : CSV voyage plans
deactivate Tracce
VisirRunner --> VisirAPI : 200 OK {routes}
deactivate VisirRunner
VisirAPI --> Pipeline : {dist: [...], time: [...], CO2t: [...]}
deactivate VisirAPI

== Step 5: viz ==

Pipeline -> Pipeline : _build_route_geojson(routes)\n_build_route_summary(routes)

deactivate Pipeline

== Progress Polling ==

loop every 500ms while job is running
  Browser -> Callbacks : poll_route_progress()
  Callbacks -> Pipeline : get_job(job_id)
  Pipeline --> Callbacks : {step, status, progress}
  Callbacks --> Browser : Update progress bar\nand step indicators
end

== Route Display ==

Browser -> Browser : Render GeoJSON on map\n(3 LineString routes\n+ start/end markers)
Browser --> User : Display route info panel\n(distance, time, CO₂\nfor each route)

@enduml
